<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-794-383  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 794 383.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Telephony  Dec 10 1990 v219 n25 p36(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Control your costs. ( telecommunication service providers)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Foreman, John C.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Companies who fail to control costs are likely to lose marketshare to the competition.andP;  In telecommunications, incentiveregulations allow service providers the opportunity to increaseprofits through cost efficiencies.andP;  Most service providers todayare attempting to reduce costs.andP;  A major problem that is incurredin cost-cutting attempts is the use of obsolete data.andP;  Inaddition, inconsistent and incomplete cost reports end upsupplying management with faulty information to work with.andP;  Someanalysts believe the major problem for service providers inreducing costs is the lack of understanding in the basic theoriesof cost management.andP;  In addition, deregulation and marketcompetition are forcing more innovative management practises interms of cost control.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Telephone companiesTelecommunicationsCommunications Service SuppliersCost ReductionManagement Style.andO;Feature:   illustrationtable.andO;Caption:   A customer's perspective of a provider. (table)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>